         <div type="comments">
            <p>
               <note type="philcomment">This fragment is a writing excercise of some very untrained scribe, cf. for instance <hi>palainne</hi> (a1) which is obviously a mistake for <hi>pelaikne</hi>. For line b2 cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkas4b"/>: b2 (= PK NS 120; S-supp or 500.3 in <bibl><title corresp="ref:levi1933"/></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1966a"/></bibl> incorrectly calls this fragment S8).</note>
               <note type="remarks">According to <bibl><title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/><citedRange>277</citedRange></bibl> "[t]he manuscript is written in a very bad, untutored hand. Medium sized ductus, clearly preserved. The recto has three lines, and verso only two lines."</note>
               <note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment"><hi>wri</hi>: curved stroke above.</note>
               <note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>pakāna</hi>: <hi>na</hi> added below.</note>
            </p>
